## Unit 3: Lesson 30 - An Introduction to Arrays

# Background

Variables are ill-suited for storing lists. However, arrays can solve many of the shortcomings of trying to use a variable to store multiple items. The array index is important. It begins at 0 and is used to access the items in an array and it defines the length of an array.

# Lesson

* Learn how to design arrays to hold a variety of information.
* Create an array in App Lab. 



